<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Swenson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-11-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I would advise you to accept clause Article I beginning “no
                            responsibility”, and to reject concluding part from “with a view”.
                            Further delay dangerous owing to attitude of Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Swenson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>